## Step-by-Step Upgrade Workflow

### When Upgrading Spring Boot 3.5.x with Redis

1. **Check if project uses Redis**:

   ```bash
   grep -r "bitso.commons:redis\|jedis\|JedisWrapper" --include="*.gradle" --include="*.toml"
   ```

2. **Update version catalog** (`gradle/libs.versions.toml`):

   ```toml
   [versions]
   spring-boot = "3.5.8"
   bitso-commons-redis = "4.2.1"
   jedis4-utils = "3.0.0"
   ```

3. **Build and test**:

   ```bash
   ./gradlew clean build -x test --no-daemon
   ./gradlew test --no-daemon
   ```

4. **If NoSuchMethodError occurs**, verify library versions:

   ```bash
   ./gradlew dependencies | grep -i "jedis\|redis"
   ```

5. **Ensure version alignment**:

   ```bash
   # Generate dependency graph
   ./gradlew -I gradle/dependency-graph-init.gradle \
       --dependency-verification=off \
       --no-configuration-cache \
       --no-configure-on-demand \
       :ForceDependencyResolutionPlugin_resolveAllDependencies

   # Check Redis/Jedis versions
   grep -i "jedis\|redis" build/reports/dependency-graph-snapshots/dependency-list.txt | sort -u
   ```

